REVENUE MODEL ARCHITECTURE

The optimal approach creates four distinct revenue streams, each with
different margin profiles and scaling characteristics:

Stream 1: Direct Hardware Sales (Highest Margin)

**Strategy:** Negotiate wholesale pricing directly with Yale, Schlage,
and Kwikset. Sell at retail or slight discount to landlords through
platform.

-   **Wholesale discount:** 25-40% off retail from manufacturers

-   **Retail to landlord:** 5-10% below Amazon for competitive
    positioning

-   **Net margin:** 15-30% per unit (\$40-\$90 per lock)

-   **Volume threshold:** 100+ units/quarter to unlock tier pricing

Stream 2: Installation Network (Recurring + Referral)

**Strategy:** Build preferred installer network. Two models available:

Model A: Referral Network (Lower Effort)

-   Partner with 5-10 licensed NYC locksmiths/handymen

-   Negotiated rate: \$80-120 per standard install

-   RealRiches referral fee: 20-25% (\$16-\$30 per install)

-   Landlord pays installer directly

Model B: White-Label Installation (Higher Margin)

-   RealRiches-branded installation service

-   Charge landlord: \$150-200 (install only) or \$400-550 (lock +
    install)

-   Pay installer: \$60-80 per job

-   Net margin: \$90-120 per installation

Stream 3: Enterprise Building Partnerships

**Strategy:** Become ButterflyMX certified installer and referral
partner for multi-unit buildings.

-   **ButterflyMX referral:** Negotiated commission on \$30-42/unit/year
    SaaS (target 10-15%)

-   **Hardware installation:** \$2,000-\$10,000+ per building project

-   **Recurring revenue:** Annual referral fees compound as buildings
    renew

-   **Example 50-unit building:** \$7,000 initial + \$300-600/year
    recurring

Stream 4: Premium Feature Subscription

**Strategy:** Self-showing features included in premium landlord tier,
driving subscription upgrades.

-   **Basic self-showing:** Free with any listing (drives adoption)

-   **Premium features:** \$29-49/month per property

-   Advanced analytics, multi-property dashboard, priority support

-   AI-powered showing optimization, automated follow-up

SECURITY ARCHITECTURE

Security is non-negotiable for community trust. Here\'s the
enterprise-grade security stack:

Pre-Showing Verification (5-Layer Security)

1.  **Government ID Upload:** Photo of valid ID (driver\'s license,
    passport)

2.  **AI Facial Recognition:** Live selfie matched against ID photo

3.  **Credit Card Hold:** \$50-100 authorization (not charged) to deter
    fraud

4.  **Phone Verification:** SMS code to verified mobile number

5.  **Background Screen:** Optional instant criminal check via API
    partner

Access Code Security

-   **Time-bound codes:** Valid only during scheduled showing window
    (±15 min buffer)

-   **Single-use enforcement:** Code expires after one successful unlock

-   **Geolocation gating:** Code only works when user is within 100m of
    property

-   **Real-time notifications:** Landlord alerted on entry/exit

-   **Audit trail:** Complete log with timestamps, stored 365 days

NYC Legal Compliance

**Critical:** NYC tenants have successfully sued landlords over smart
lock privacy concerns. Our platform addresses this:

-   **Physical key backup:** All recommended locks support physical key
    access

-   **Privacy-first design:** Minimal data retention, clear disclosure

-   **Opt-in only:** Landlords explicitly enable self-showing

-   **FARE Act compliant:** Integrated with RealRiches disclosure
    workflows

Technical Security Standards

-   **Encryption:** AES-256 for all data at rest, TLS 1.3 in transit

-   **API security:** OAuth 2.0, rate limiting, IP allowlisting

-   **Lock communication:** Seam handles all device-level encryption

-   **SOC 2 alignment:** Seam is SOC 2 compliant

